-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/brazil-agency-names-firm-to-assess-oil-reserves-to-sell-to-petrobras.html

          
          
             Brazilâ€™s oil regulator said its
board authorized hiring a firm to evaluate the size of offshore
crude reserves that the government plans to swap for new shares
in state-controlled producer Petroleo Brasileiro SA.  
 The ANP, as the regulator is known, said today in an e-mail
that it hired Gaffney, Cline & Associates Inc. to evaluate the
pre-salt reserves by the end of August.  
